  "text": "# Firefox TLS Handshake Chain: Necko to NSS\n\n## Complete Chain Summary\n\nThe Firefox TLS connection flow from networking layer to cryptographic layer proceeds through these distinct hops:\n\n### 1. **HTTP Connection Initiation (netwerk/protocol/http/)**\n   - **File**: `nsHttpConnection.h` (class definition at line 52)\n   - **Key Class**: `nsHttpConnection`\n   - **Function**: Represents a connection to an HTTP/HTTPS server. For HTTPS connections, it orchestrates the TLS handshake.\n   - **Related**: Includes `TlsHandshaker.h` (line 21) which coordinates SSL setup and parameter initialization.\n   - **Key Method in TlsHandshaker**: `SetupSSL()` (line 26) and `InitSSLParams()` (line 27)\n\n### 2. **Socket Provider Bridge (security/manager/ssl/)**\n   - **File**: `nsSSLSocketProvider.cpp` (and `nsTLSSocketProvider.cpp`)\n   - **Function**: Socket provider service that creates SSL-enabled sockets by calling `nsSSLIOLayerAddToSocket()` at line 41-44\n   - **Purpose**: Bridges Firefox's socket layer to NSS SSL/TLS functionality\n\n### 3. **SSL I/O Layer Helpers (security/manager/ssl/nsNSSIOLayer.h)**\n   - **File**: `nsNSSIOLayer.h` and `nsNSSIOLayer.cpp`\n   - **Key Class**: `nsSSLIOLayerHelpers` (class definition at line 38 in .h file)\n   - **Function**: Manages NSS I/O layer state, configuration, and TLS intolerance handling\n   - **Static Members**:\n     - `nsSSLIOLayerIdentity` (line 52) - Identifies the SSL I/O layer\n     - `nsSSLPlaintextLayerIdentity` (line 53) - Identifies the plaintext observer layer\n     - `nsSSLIOLayerMethods` and `nsSSLPlaintextLayerMethods` - I/O method stubs\n   - **Purpose**: Bridges Firefox networking (Necko) to NSS cryptographic layer\n\n### 4. **SSL Socket Initialization (security/manager/ssl/nsNSSIOLayer.cpp)**\n   - **File**: `nsNSSIOLayer.cpp`\n   - **Key Function**: `nsSSLIOLayerAddToSocket()` (line 1790)\n   - **Process**:\n     1. Creates `nsSSLIOLayerHelpers` instance (lines 1797-1807)\n     2. Creates `NSSSocketControl` wrapper (lines 1809-1811) that holds socket state\n     3. Pushes plaintext observer layer (lines 1835-1856)\n     4. Calls `nsSSLIOLayerImportFD()` to create SSL socket (line 1859)\n     5. Calls `nsSSLIOLayerSetOptions()` to configure TLS version, cipher suites, etc. (line 1864)\n     6. Pushes NSS SSL I/O layer (lines 1871-1897)\n   - **Related File**: `NSSSocketControl.h` - Holds per-socket TLS state and security info\n\n### 5. **NSS Socket Creation (security/manager/ssl/nsNSSIOLayer.cpp)**\n   - **File**: `nsNSSIOLayer.cpp`\n   - **Key Function**: `nsSSLIOLayerImportFD()` (line 1269)\n   - **Critical Calls**:\n     - Line 1274: `SSL_ImportFD(nullptr, fd)` - **Bridges to NSS**: Creates NSS SSL socket wrapper\n     - Lines 1278-1309: Sets up NSS callbacks:\n       - `SSL_HandshakeCallback()` - Called when handshake completes\n       - `SSL_SecretCallback()` - Called with handshake secrets (TLS 1.3)\n       - `SSL_AuthCertificateHook()` - Called for server certificate verification\n       - `SSL_GetClientAuthDataHook()` - Called for client certificate selection\n       - `SSL_SetURL()` - Sets server hostname for SNI\n\n### 6. **TLS Handshake Driver (security/nss/lib/ssl/sslsecur.c)**\n   - **File**: `sslsecur.c`\n   - **Key Function**: `ssl_Do1stHandshake()` (line 32)\n   - **Process**:\n     - Loop starting at line 37: `while (ss->handshake && rv == SECSuccess)`\n     - Line 43: `rv = (*ss->handshake)(ss)` - Calls the current handshake state machine function\n     - Executes state machines from client/server hello through key exchange to finished messages\n     - Returns control to application via callbacks\n   - **Related Function**: `ssl_FinishHandshake()` (line 53) - Called when handshake completes\n\n### 7. **SSL3/TLS Protocol Implementation (security/nss/lib/ssl/ssl3con.c)**\n   - **File**: `ssl3con.c`\n   - **Purpose**: Implements TLS 1.0-1.2 handshake protocol\n   - **Key Content**:\n     - Lines 97-100+: Cipher suite configuration and policy\n